-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- OBSERVATIONS
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў= obs-fact-check-convergence
  вҲҙ The вҠўвҲҳ fact-check-loop converged in 2 iterations of max 3. Iteration 1
    identified 2 factual errors out of 18 claims (11% error rate). Both were
    precision errors вҖ” not outright fabrications but insufficiently precise
    attributions. After surgical correction (replacing only the 2 failed
    sentences), all 18 claims passed in iteration 2. The loop demonstrates
    monotonic improvement: the correction does not introduce new errors.

вҠў= obs-spawner-as-parallel-oracle
  вҲҙ The spawn-fact-checkers cell creates 18 independent oracle cells, one per
    claim. These are all independently evaluable (no cross-dependencies), making
    this a maximally parallel execution pattern. In a real Cell runtime, all 18
    could execute simultaneously. This is the "embarrassingly parallel" oracle
    pattern: break one complex verification task (article fact-checking) into N
    independent simple verifications. The spawner transforms a monolithic quality
    gate into a fine-grained, parallelizable verification mesh.

вҠў= obs-error-taxonomy
  вҲҙ Two categories of factual error detected:
    (1) Date precision: BitKeeper "created in 1998" conflated company founding
    with product release. The corrected claim distinguishes "founded company 1998"
    from "released product 2000". This is a common LLM error pattern вҖ” temporal
    conflation of related events.
    (2) Attribution scope: GitHub "launched by" four people included Scott Chacon,
    who was an early employee, not a co-founder. The LLM included a prominent
    associated person who wasn't in the founding group. This is the "halo
    attribution" error вҖ” nearby prominent figures get absorbed into origin stories.

вҠў= obs-surgical-rewriting
  вҲҙ The rewrite-article cell performs surgical replacement: only sentences
    containing failed claims are modified. The 16 passing claims and their
    surrounding prose are preserved verbatim. This locality property is critical
    for convergence вҖ” if rewriting destabilized adjacent sentences, the loop
    could oscillate. The вҠЁ oracle "length(claims') = length(claims)" enforces
    structural stability: no claims can be added or removed during correction,
    only content-modified.

вҠў= obs-verification-cheaper-than-generation
  вҲҙ Generating the article (1 LLM call) produced 18 claims. Verifying required
    18 independent fact-checks. In terms of Cell's computational model: generation
    is a single soft cell, verification is N soft cells. Each individual
    fact-check is simpler than the original generation (checking a single claim
    vs writing a coherent multi-paragraph article). This mirrors the NP/P
    asymmetry from proof-carrying computation: producing the article is hard,
    checking each claim is comparatively easy. The spawner pattern makes this
    asymmetry explicit and exploitable.

вҠў= obs-loop-as-editorial-process
  вҲҙ The вҠўвҲҳ fact-check-loop models a real editorial fact-checking workflow:
    (1) Writer produces draft (generate-article)
    (2) Fact-checkers independently verify claims (spawn-fact-checkers)
    (3) Editor aggregates results (aggregate-results)
    (4) Writer revises only flagged passages (rewrite-article)
    (5) Repeat until clean (вҠўвҲҳ until all-pass)
    Cell's contribution is making this workflow executable, traceable, and
    convergent. Each iteration's state is a hashable document. The editorial
    process becomes a formal fixed-point computation.
